contentrichtext.text: <!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------> <!-- MoS:Disambiguation - prefer ONE LINK per entry, short descriptions. --> <!-- Avoid piping, external links, and red links with little article potential --> <!-------------------------------------------------------------------------------> {{wiktionarypar|blowout|blow out}} '''Blowout''' or '''Blow out''' can refer to: ==Science and technology== *[[Blowout (well drilling)]], a sudden release of oil and gas from a well *[[Blowout (geology)]], a sandy depression caused by the removal of sediment by wind *[[Blowout grass]], a grass found on sand dunes *[[Blowout fracture]], a type of skull fracture *[[Blowout (tire)]], a sudden loss of tire pressure ==Media== *''[[Blow Out]]'', a 1981 film directed by Brian De Palma *[[Blow Out (TV series)|''Blow Out'' (TV series)]], on Bravo network *"Blow Out", a song from Radiohead's ''[[Pablo Honey]]'' *"Blowout", a 2001 song from The Crystal Method's ''[[Tweekend]]'' *''[[BlowOut]]'', a 2004 video game * "Blowout", an episode of the TV series ''[[Mayday (TV series)|Mayday]]'' about British Airways Flight 5390 * ''Blowout'', a novel by [[Byron Dorgan]] and [[David Hagberg]] ==Other== *[[Blowout (hairstyle)]] *[[Blowout (sports)]], an easy or one-sided victory * Blown out highlights in a photograph, also called [[clipping (photography)|clipping]] * Blowout, an ink blur in a [[tattoo]] * Blow-out, another name for a [[party horn]] {{disambig}}
